<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="733" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2633: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-20T19:00:00-05:00">November 20, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>76. Your 353, November 20, 11 a.m. The completely independent
                                    course being followed by the United States should by now be well
                                    understood in Geneva. Any procedure in connection with any part
                                    of the program of the Coordination Committee or Committee of
                                    Eighteen would, of course, have no relation to any action by
                                    this Government taken in accordance with our well-established
                                    policy of non-entanglement and neutrality. There would certainly
                                    seem to be no reason for Vasconcellos to approach you in this
                                    matter in view of our well-known position.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>